<module>
    <h>dorus</h>
    <p><g>dorus</g>
        <en>door</en> is a masculine <a href="?xx=nouns/simple_common_nouns">simple common
        noun</a>.</p>

    <section id="forms">
        <h>forms</h>
        <p>The principal parts of <g>dorus</g> are – <ul>
                <li><m>dorus</m> – nominative/dative singular</li>
                <li><m>doruis</m> – genitive singular</li>
                <li><m>dorsan</m> – plural</li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <section id="definiteness">
            <h>definiteness</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>indefinite <ul>
                            <li>singular <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bun <m>doruis</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>plural <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bunan <m>dhorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>definite <ul>
                            <li>singular <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>an dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>an dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bun <m>an doruis</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>plural <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>na dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>na dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bunan <m>nan dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
        <section id="number">
            <h>number</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>singular <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bun <m>doruis</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>an dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>an dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bun <m>an doruis</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>plural <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>doruis</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bunan <m>dhorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>nominative – <m>na dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>dative – aig <m>na dorsan</m></li>
                                    <li>genitive – bunan <m>nan dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
        <section id="case">
            <h>case</h>
            <p><ul>
                    <li>nominative <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – <m>dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – <m>dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – <m>an dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – <m>na dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>dative <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – aig <m>dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – aig <m>dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – aig <m>an dorus</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – aig <m>na dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                    <li>genitive <ul>
                            <li>indefinite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – bun <m>doruis</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – bunan <m>dhorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                            <li>definite <ul>
                                    <li>singular – bun <m>an doruis</m></li>
                                    <li>plural – bunan <m>nan dorsan</m></li>
                                </ul></li>
                        </ul></li>
                </ul></p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h>notes</h>
            <p>Note that in post-1970s Neo-Gaelic, the forms <g>dorus</g> and <g>doruis</g> have
                been standardised to <g>doras</g> and <g>dorais</g> respectively.</p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>dependents</h>
        <section id="deps-spr">
            <h>specifier</h>
            <p><g>dorus</g> can occur with a specifier.</p>
            <p>Examples with the definite article – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha <m>an dorus</m> mór.</gd>
                        <tr>The door is big.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cù aig <m>an dorus</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>The dog is at the door.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Chunnaic mi cù aig <m>an dorus</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>I saw a dog at the door.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an cù aig <m>an dorus</m>?</gd>
                        <tr>Is the dog at the door?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 11</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h>uses</h>
        <section id="uses-sbj">
            <h>subject</h>
            <p><g>dorus</g> can be used as the subject of a verb.</p>
            <p>Examples with <a href="?gd=bi"><g>bi</g></a> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an <m>dorus</m> mór.</gd>
                        <tr>The door is big.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
        <section id="uses-comp">
            <h>complement</h>
            <p><g>dorus</g> can be used as the complement of a preposition.</p>
            <p>Some examples with <g><a href="?gd=aig">aig</a> dorus</g>
                <en>at a door</en> – <xl>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Tha an cù dubh <m>aig an dorus</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>The black dog is at the door.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 9</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>Chunnaic mi cù <m>aig an dorus</m>.</gd>
                        <tr>I saw a dog at the door.</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 6</ref>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <gd>A bheil an cù <m>aig an dorus</m>?</gd>
                        <tr>Is the dog at the door?</tr>
                        <ref text="617">td. 11</ref>
                    </li>
                </xl>
            </p>
        </section>
    </section>

</module>
